I’m not a fan of Donald Trump. I think he’s an arrogant, self-centered, narcissistic jerk who has no business being president. But that doesn’t mean he isn’t fit to be president. The Constitution says nothing about the character or personality traits of those who hold public office. It only requires that they meet certain qualifications: 1. Be at least thirty-five years old;
2. Have been a citizen of the United States for fourteen years; and
3. Reside in the state from which they are elected. Trump meets all three requirements. He’s forty-five years old (he turned fifty on June 14), was born in New York City, and resides there now. So what’s the problem?

